1
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:05,920
<i>I must go there to search for something.</i>

2
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,240
What is it? Tell me.

3
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:09,639
It is Klaikot Lek Lai.

4
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:13,840
Uncle Chaem told you
to stay and attend to me.

5
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:15,760
My father told me to keep you company,

6
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,560
<i>not to be your servant.</i>

7
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:21,800
<i>- I'm going to kill Pud.</i>
<i>- Once you kill Pud,</i>

8
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:25,240
your secret dies with him.

9
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:33,440
<i>Tonight, our son will finally have a wife.</i>

10
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:35,400
What is this?

11
00:02:35,480 --> 00:02:38,240
<i>Spirits of the dead, unite with the living</i>

12
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:53,920
I'm starting to wonder

13
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,000
if you're still
the same Blur I used to know?

14
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:00,480
Why?

15
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:03,000
When you killed those two,

16
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:05,840
your eyes didn't look like yours.

17
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:13,840
Blur!

18
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:23,360
Everything I've been through
has taught me one thing,

19
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:27,000
only the strong survive.

20
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:30,880
If we don't kill them, they'll kill us.

21
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:36,120
In the year we were apart,

22
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:39,840
you must've gone through a lot.

23
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:51,040
And because of that,
my purpose is clearer than ever.

24
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:54,880
To learn sorcery at Khao Phrom

25
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:57,840
and find the Klaikot Lek Lai.

26
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:01,920
The old saying goes,
"Dark Lek Lai drives men mad,

27
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:05,120
rambling nonsense, dabbling in alchemy,

28
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,760
till their clothes are torn to shreds."

29
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:11,000
What if the Lek Lai you're chasing
doesn't even exist?

30
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:28,200
This map,
Old Master Khrua Phut gave it to me.

31
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:43,520
This map will lead you
to the Klaikot Lek Lai cave.

32
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:46,800
Whether you find it or not

33
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:49,000
depends on your fate.

34
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:52,640
Something this precious…

35
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:55,640
why give it to me?

36
00:04:56,400 --> 00:05:00,920
These are corrupt times.

37
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,480
The wicked rise to power.

38
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:05,280
Use the power of the Lek Lai

39
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:08,040
to help the helpless,

40
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:10,520
and be a refuge for those in distress.

41
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:18,640
And if I fail to find it?

42
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:22,040
Then abandon this path

43
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:25,360
and never return to Tha Khiri again.

44
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,880
We're here.
If we follow the stream upstream,

45
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:30,880
we'll reach the Lek Lai cave.

46
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:34,360
The deeper we go,
the more dangerous it becomes.

47
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:37,120
Are you sure
you want to risk your life with me?

48
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:41,400
Whether it's heaven or hell,

49
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,440
I'm going with you.

50
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:58,160
And you're not afraid
I'm no longer the same Blur?

51
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:05,000
You may have changed, but I trust you.

52
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:09,920
Why do you trust me?

53
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:15,400
I almost died,
and you risked your life to save me.

54
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:19,040
I know this man

55
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:21,520
would never let anything happen to me.

56
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:31,400
Let's go. Maybe my brother
has already reached the cave.

57
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:41,040
The Siamese government
will build a railway from Bangkok

58
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:44,040
to the port to expand trade.

59
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:48,440
Soon, my city
will surpass every southern city.

60
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:52,760
I've already bought up
all the land along the route.

61
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:55,800
Any investment will pay off.

62
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,440
Your Excellency,

63
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:02,680
If progress arrives, I fear
governing will only become more difficult.

64
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:06,520
The authorities will send
their own people in. And if that happens…

65
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,400
As long as Your Excellency
remains governor,

66
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:12,440
there's nothing to fear.

67
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:16,800
Or does Khun Paeng doubt your authority?

68
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:21,920
Huh, Tim.

69
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:25,280
If you're so scared,
go home and raise buffalo.

70
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:29,320
I'll make Pae the new Khun Paeng instead.

71
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:34,080
Big ambitions, tiny courage.

72
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:37,120
No wonder Khun Paeng never rises.

73
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:43,280
I'll turn Tha Khiri
into a city of pleasure,

74
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:46,560
casinos, brothels,
liquor dens, opium halls.

75
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:50,280
We'll bring in foreign traders,

76
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:52,720
Chinese, Arab,

77
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:55,840
and Westerners, to invest here.

78
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,280
What do you say?

79
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:00,880
That sounds good.

80
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:02,240
I'm good at trade.

81
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:08,640
Just let me be the tax collector.

82
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:32,440
Two of my prophecies
have already come true.

83
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:37,640
First, within three days,
your wife will die by a venomous creature.

84
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,600
Second,

85
00:08:39,679 --> 00:08:43,799
your son will bring great ruin
upon Chum Suea.

86
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:51,280
Only one remains. Just one more.

87
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,360
That's not a prophecy.

88
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,000
It's a curse.

89
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:58,920
Prophecy or curse,

90
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,000
you cannot escape it.

91
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:05,720
Those twins

92
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:08,720
share a bound fate.

93
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:13,160
If one dies, the other will follow

94
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,440
within three days, seven at most.

95
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,480
I surrender.

96
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,640
Whoever you are,

97
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:53,880
please save my children.

98
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:59,720
Please, Grandma. Any sin,

99
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:04,040
let me bear it for them.

100
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:09,280
Even if it costs me my life.

101
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:12,240
You don't need to beg.

102
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:15,000
Death is already waiting ahead.

103
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:19,000
Use what time you have left

104
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,880
wisely.

105
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:07,160
- This must be the cave.
- How do you know?

106
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:12,200
It's too clean, too peaceful.

107
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:15,240
No birds, no rats, no bats.

108
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:19,400
Cool, damp air. Perfect for Lek Lai.

109
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:24,280
Does the map say what to do next?

110
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:26,160
It does.

111
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:36,840
"Kindle the flame toward the southwest.

112
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:41,240
Below the cave shaft, stars aglow.

113
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:44,520
The tragic legend of Meri's death.

114
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:48,320
At dusk, honey drips.
The ore begins to flow."

115
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:52,040
What does it mean?
I don't understand any of it.

116
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:55,760
Lek Lai is more powerful than any sorcery.

117
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:59,560
Only by following the proper order
can one claim it.

118
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:04,200
That's why it's written in riddles.

119
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:11,800
"Kindle the flame toward the southwest…"

120
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:17,720
Southwest?

121
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:30,080
So we light a torch and head southwest.

122
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,120
Hold my hand.

123
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:43,560
Hold your hand? Does the map say that too?

124
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:49,440
No. I just want to hold your hand
so you won't run away.

125
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:56,720
After coming this far,

126
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:59,800
I wouldn't know
how to find my way back anyway.

127
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:34,120
Your daughter is not here.

128
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:40,160
I've searched for her in every direction,

129
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:44,600
yet found no trace.
I don't know if she's alive or dead.

130
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:52,440
People suffer because of their thoughts.

131
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:54,240
If you do not think, you do not suffer.

132
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:57,840
For now, your daughter is safe.

133
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:01,880
Go back. When the time comes,
you will meet her yourself.

134
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:17,840
Once the railway cuts through here,
Chum Suea will really come alive.

135
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:20,880
It'll be even easier to rob
the merchants passing through.

136
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:24,640
Pae, if you keep robbing merchants,
when will you ever get rich?

137
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:28,920
Brothels and gambling dens,
that's where the real money is.

138
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:30,840
Oh.

139
00:14:30,920 --> 00:14:33,240
Such a goldmine like that,

140
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:35,040
will the Governor really allow it?

141
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:37,760
Why wouldn't he? Can't we all share?

142
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:40,400
I've dealt with both Khun Yod
and Bandit Wad.

143
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:43,640
All the credit he gets is because of me.

144
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:46,960
Then I suppose I should
reward you properly, Bandit Pud.

145
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:48,800
Hey?

146
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,200
Who's there? Show yourself!

147
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:55,920
Hey!

148
00:14:58,120 --> 00:15:00,600
Hey, Uncle.

149
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:11,120
Whoa, Lasor.

150
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:13,800
I'll take him, Uncle.

151
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:30,360
You had the nerve
to destroy my father's Chum Suea.

152
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:32,600
And you used me to kill Khun Yod.

153
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,200
That's because
you were stupid enough to fall for it.

154
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:40,000
I was stupid

155
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:43,480
because I wasn't vile enough
to match a bastard like you.

156
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:45,600
What do you want?

157
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:48,400
I want your life.

158
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:52,000
Hah. It won't be that easy.

159
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:12,160
Pud, your Saming Eye
can't touch me anymore.

160
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:18,200
Lasor, don't kill me!

161
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:21,920
I didn't mean to do it! Phraya Decha

162
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:25,360
and Khun Paeng forced me.
I didn't want to do it!

163
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:27,080
If they ordered you to die,

164
00:16:27,160 --> 00:16:29,520
would you?

165
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:34,080
I'm scared. I'm scared!

166
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:38,120
<i>Nisa-wasu.</i>

167
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:50,160
Pud, you won't escape me.

168
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:00,920
At least you only lost one eye.

169
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:03,800
Instead of helping me,

170
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:06,760
you let that bastard rip my eye out.
You damn nephew!

171
00:17:06,839 --> 00:17:09,520
Whoa, Uncle. What could I do?

172
00:17:09,599 --> 00:17:12,440
Even your Saming Eye couldn't touch him.

173
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:15,720
His sorcery is terrifying.

174
00:17:16,839 --> 00:17:19,040
Where did he learn such power?

175
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,599
Wherever he learned it doesn't matter.

176
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:26,040
What matters is that he won't spare us.

177
00:17:26,119 --> 00:17:28,680
Then I must report this to the governor.

178
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:33,040
Uncle, you rest here. I'll go myself.

179
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:49,520
These must be the ones
who came searching for Lek Lai

180
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:51,160
and never found their way out.

181
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:55,800
I hope my brother never came in here.

182
00:18:03,680 --> 00:18:04,760
Blur.

183
00:18:04,840 --> 00:18:08,840
Look. The path we walked in on is gone.

184
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:17,200
We can only move forward now.
There's no turning back.

185
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:19,680
Do you know the way?

186
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:37,800
What did you say, Pae?

187
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:40,400
Lasor, Bandit Wad's son, has returned.

188
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:44,760
Then what was your Uncle Pud doing?

189
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:47,600
Lasor gouged out his eye.

190
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:49,480
He's being treated now.

191
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:54,520
He's coming for revenge
for the men I had hanged.

192
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:57,120
I'll deploy the police to hunt Lasor down

193
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:59,160
and reinforce your security.

194
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:02,160
Find capable men
to protect my daughters as well.

195
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:03,240
Yes, sir.

196
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:23,680
Yeah.

197
00:19:27,840 --> 00:19:30,480
Noree woke up before dawn
just to cook this for you.

198
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,560
I was worried
the meat wouldn't be tender enough.

199
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:36,280
I'd be embarrassed if it wasn't good.

200
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:40,680
Eat up. Don't you have duty after this?

201
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:43,640
There's robbery every single day now.

202
00:19:44,360 --> 00:19:46,680
When people are desperate,
they turn into bandits.

203
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:50,960
With so few police,
how can you fight them?

204
00:19:52,080 --> 00:19:53,520
You can't win against bandits.

205
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:05,320
It's delicious.

206
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:07,480
You're a great cook, Noree.

207
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:12,560
If you like it, have more.
You'll need strength to catch criminals.

208
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:20,080
Noree would make a perfect housewife.

209
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:23,960
She never falls short
when it comes to household duties.

210
00:20:24,040 --> 00:20:27,680
Anyone who marries her
will live easy for life.

211
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:29,560
Interested?

212
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:37,720
Pun, orders just came in.

213
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:41,520
We're to report to Phraya Dechanurak,
the Governor of Tha Khiri.

214
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:44,400
- When?
- Now.

215
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:58,400
I'm thinking of inviting merchants
from other towns

216
00:20:58,480 --> 00:21:00,200
to buy local products

217
00:21:00,280 --> 00:21:01,960
and setting up a trading company

218
00:21:02,040 --> 00:21:04,840
to trade with Penang and Malaya.

219
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:06,400
What do you think?

220
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:09,480
Good.

221
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:16,000
Besides pepper, I'm planning
to buy coconuts, betel nuts, nutmeg,

222
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:19,040
and coffee as well. What do you think?

223
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:20,440
Good.

224
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:22,680
Hey.

225
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:24,520
Don't you know how to say anything else?

226
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:28,480
I'm a barber's son,
not a merchant's son like you.

227
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:31,120
What would I know about trade?

228
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:36,040
Honestly, I don't even
want to be a merchant.

229
00:21:36,120 --> 00:21:38,080
But my dad forced me.

230
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:40,560
He wants me
to inherit the family business.

231
00:21:41,760 --> 00:21:43,640
If not a merchant,
what would you want to be?

232
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:46,920
I want to be

233
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:49,360
a painter.

234
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:52,600
That won't even put food on the table.

235
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:55,320
Being a wealthy tycoon is much better.

236
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:57,200
Far more comfortable.

237
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:01,800
Money can't buy everything.

238
00:22:01,880 --> 00:22:04,880
But without money, you can't buy anything.

239
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,240
So I'd rather have money.

240
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:12,920
You're right.

241
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:16,040
Money isn't everything,

242
00:22:16,880 --> 00:22:19,840
but everything starts with money.

243
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:29,560
It's getting late. I'm heading back.

244
00:22:32,320 --> 00:22:33,240
Wait.

245
00:22:44,280 --> 00:22:47,360
I couldn't sleep last night.

246
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:49,320
Come stay over with me tonight.

247
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:24,040
That way. The wind's coming from that way.
There must be an exit. Let's go.

248
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:33,960
I'm so cold I can barely walk.

249
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:42,880
Then rest here. I'll make a fire.

250
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:07,080
"Below the cave shaft, stars aglow…"

251
00:24:08,120 --> 00:24:09,200
Blur.

252
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:13,120
Over there.

253
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:18,880
The cave shaft.

254
00:24:19,880 --> 00:24:22,560
That's it. This must be the place.

255
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:25,160
We're on the right path.

256
00:24:52,280 --> 00:24:53,600
The fire won't light.

257
00:24:54,640 --> 00:24:58,960
Could this be
the next riddle from the map?

258
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:05,280
"The tragic legend of Meri's death."

259
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:09,960
What is the tragic legend of Meri?

260
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:17,720
"She spoke, her body growing weak,

261
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:21,760
collapsed upon the cliff's edge.

262
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:26,040
Her heart suffocated,
her breath withheld.

263
00:25:26,120 --> 00:25:29,640
Meri died upon the mountain peak."

264
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:35,240
So how did Meri die, Yiam?

265
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:40,240
She died from holding her breath.
That's what the verse says.

266
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:44,960
According to the legend,
Meri died from holding her breath.

267
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:50,360
Then maybe… we have to hold our breath
while lighting the fire.

268
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:52,360
Try it.

269
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,600
It worked.

270
00:26:10,080 --> 00:26:13,480
"Kindle the flame toward the southwest.

271
00:26:13,560 --> 00:26:16,640
Below the cave shaft, stars aglow.

272
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:20,040
The tragic legend of Meri's death.

273
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:23,760
At dusk, honey drips.
The ore begins to flow."

274
00:26:25,800 --> 00:26:28,440
Hold your breath
and light the fire to the southwest,

275
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:32,960
beneath the cave shaft at night
when the stars shine…

276
00:26:34,040 --> 00:26:36,320
Then the Lek Lai will descend
to drink honey.

277
00:26:39,080 --> 00:26:40,000
Honey.

278
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:03,400
<i>Om, sawa hom mama mama</i>
<i>narakja cittang phanthanang.</i>

279
00:27:12,480 --> 00:27:14,200
Did you chant it wrong, Blur?

280
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:21,640
No. I remember every word.

281
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:27,640
Or maybe…
we still haven't solved all of it.

282
00:27:32,320 --> 00:27:36,240
"Kindle the flame toward the southwest.

283
00:27:36,320 --> 00:27:39,160
Below the cave shaft, stars aglow.

284
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:42,960
The tragic legend of Meri's death.

285
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:47,000
At dusk, honey drips.
The ore begins to flow."

286
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:53,640
Under the stump.

287
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:42,640
<i>Om, sawa hom mama mama</i>
<i>narakja cittang phanthanang.</i>

288
00:29:34,160 --> 00:29:35,320
Blur!

289
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:26,200
Blur.

290
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:47,440
I'm cold.

291
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:52,240
- I'm cold…
- Blur.

292
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:57,080
What should I do?

293
00:32:01,120 --> 00:32:02,360
Help me…

294
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:08,880
Please don't die, Blur.

295
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:30,840
Where are you rushing off to?

296
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:35,280
Let go of me, Blur.

297
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:51,920
You were hugging me all night.

298
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:57,560
You were about to die.
What was I supposed to do?

299
00:36:59,480 --> 00:37:04,560
Then tell me,
what exactly did you do to me?

300
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:10,240
- I don't know.
- But I do.

301
00:37:12,840 --> 00:37:14,120
What do you know?

302
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:17,440
I know that…

303
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:22,840
I survived because of you.

304
00:37:28,080 --> 00:37:30,440
- Can you let me go now?
- No.

305
00:37:32,560 --> 00:37:34,760
I should've just let you die.

306
00:37:36,080 --> 00:37:39,280
If I died, you'd be a widow.

307
00:37:42,080 --> 00:37:43,720
Have you no shame?

308
00:37:44,520 --> 00:37:47,840
You're my wife already.
What's there to be shy about?

309
00:37:52,120 --> 00:37:53,280
You're shameless.

310
00:38:25,680 --> 00:38:27,440
How did I end up sleeping up here?

311
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:01,320
Eat.

312
00:39:04,880 --> 00:39:06,280
I don't eat raw eggs.

313
00:39:09,040 --> 00:39:12,640
Just eat it.
Or do you want me to feed you?

314
00:39:13,520 --> 00:39:16,840
- Here.
- No. I can eat by myself.

315
00:39:21,080 --> 00:39:24,320
Why didn't you blow on it first?
Here, water.

316
00:39:30,600 --> 00:39:33,280
This is all your fault.
My tongue's completely wrecked.

317
00:39:48,560 --> 00:39:51,040
Today I'm going
to inspect land for a warehouse.

318
00:39:53,600 --> 00:39:54,640
Come with me.

319
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,560
Why do I have to go?

320
00:39:58,640 --> 00:40:01,960
Your father told you
to look after me. You forgot already?

321
00:41:21,440 --> 00:41:23,960
- You're eating a lot.
- It's delicious.

322
00:41:39,120 --> 00:41:40,360
What's wrong?

323
00:41:41,960 --> 00:41:44,800
It feels like
something's moving inside me.

324
00:41:48,120 --> 00:41:50,720
It must be the power
of the Klaikot Lek Lai.

325
00:41:50,800 --> 00:41:53,520
I saw it vanish into your body.

326
00:41:56,560 --> 00:41:58,600
Even though I obtained it,

327
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:02,360
I don't know how to control its power.

328
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:07,120
My dad once said
Lek Lai chooses its master.

329
00:42:07,200 --> 00:42:09,040
You'll figure it out in time.

330
00:42:15,680 --> 00:42:16,640
Orror,

331
00:42:17,520 --> 00:42:19,560
if one day I change,

332
00:42:20,640 --> 00:42:22,680
if I'm no longer the Blur you know,

333
00:42:24,680 --> 00:42:26,480
will you still love me?

334
00:42:29,840 --> 00:42:31,200
Why would you ask that?

335
00:42:36,080 --> 00:42:38,120
I'm afraid I'll lose you.

336
00:42:45,440 --> 00:42:47,600
If you ever change into someone else,

337
00:42:51,800 --> 00:42:52,920
I'll be the one

338
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:55,960
who brings the real you back.

339
00:43:36,720 --> 00:43:38,960
Lasor will definitely come here.

340
00:43:39,560 --> 00:43:41,960
Go prepare black dog's blood for me.

341
00:43:42,040 --> 00:43:44,080
I'll give him a proper welcome.

342
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:50,680
Are you sure
you want to use such a dirty trick?

343
00:43:52,280 --> 00:43:53,400
I don't care.

344
00:43:54,040 --> 00:43:57,000
As long as I can take his head
to the governor, that's enough.

345
00:43:58,440 --> 00:44:00,400
It won't be as easy as you think.

346
00:44:00,480 --> 00:44:03,840
Pae, I killed Khun Yod myself.

347
00:44:03,920 --> 00:44:06,240
What can some useless kid do to me?

348
00:44:10,400 --> 00:44:13,600
You've already lost one eye.
Still not enough?

349
00:44:15,440 --> 00:44:16,400
You're not Pae!

350
00:44:22,600 --> 00:44:25,280
It's too late to realize now, Pud.

351
00:44:33,040 --> 00:44:34,160
Lasor.

352
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:39,240
Narai's Transformation Spell,
the one you said

353
00:44:39,320 --> 00:44:41,400
you'd teach me, Pud.

354
00:44:44,000 --> 00:44:45,120
What are you going to do to me?

355
00:44:46,480 --> 00:44:49,080
Did that buffalo hide taste good?

356
00:44:56,600 --> 00:44:59,800
<i>Nirujjhanti tesang vo</i>

357
00:45:00,360 --> 00:45:01,600
<i>pasamo sukho.</i>

358
00:45:25,920 --> 00:45:29,760
This is for what you did to my people.

359
00:45:35,560 --> 00:45:38,640
Uncle, I brought your favorite dried meat.

360
00:45:39,280 --> 00:45:41,800
You're sleeping this early?

361
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:54,560
Uncle… Uncle…

362
00:45:58,200 --> 00:46:02,440
Huai Yao's a small district.
You can trade whatever you want

363
00:46:02,520 --> 00:46:07,280
as long as you don't cross
Phraya Decha, the Governor of Tha Khiri,

364
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:11,800
and Thongyoo, that bloodsucking tycoon.

365
00:46:11,880 --> 00:46:16,360
The tax farmer
who monopolizes royal duties?

366
00:46:16,440 --> 00:46:17,600
That's him.

367
00:46:18,760 --> 00:46:22,840
He works with the Governor,
always scheming to fatten his own pockets.

368
00:46:22,920 --> 00:46:27,080
He doesn't care
how the common folk are squeezed dry.

369
00:46:27,160 --> 00:46:28,920
If people are suffering,
why not submit a petition?

370
00:46:29,000 --> 00:46:30,720
Who'd dare go looking for trouble?

371
00:46:31,440 --> 00:46:33,280
They've got powerful nobles backing them.

372
00:46:34,400 --> 00:46:36,360
Fight them and you'll only lose.

373
00:46:40,360 --> 00:46:44,840
Look there. Speak of the devil.

374
00:46:46,440 --> 00:46:47,520
More!

375
00:46:47,600 --> 00:46:48,480
Hurry up.

376
00:47:20,680 --> 00:47:24,200
What's going on, Duen?
Why are there police all over our house?

377
00:47:25,480 --> 00:47:28,000
Dad must've ordered them to protect us.

378
00:47:28,600 --> 00:47:30,400
Protect us from who?

379
00:47:30,480 --> 00:47:33,720
From Lasor, the son of Bandit Wad.

380
00:47:39,640 --> 00:47:43,560
I am Pun, a police officer
from Huai Yao Station.

381
00:47:44,080 --> 00:47:47,400
I will carry out my duty of protecting
you both to the best of my ability.

382
00:47:49,120 --> 00:47:52,200
It feels safer
with police protection, Duen.

383
00:47:53,720 --> 00:47:55,000
For your safety,

384
00:47:55,640 --> 00:47:58,400
you must follow police regulations.

385
00:47:59,240 --> 00:48:01,040
What regulations?

386
00:48:01,120 --> 00:48:04,880
First, you must not leave the residence
at night under any circumstances.

387
00:48:04,960 --> 00:48:06,760
You're grounding me?

388
00:48:06,840 --> 00:48:10,960
Second, you must not be alone.

389
00:48:11,040 --> 00:48:13,080
A police escort must remain
with you at all times.

390
00:48:13,160 --> 00:48:16,600
I'm not a prisoner. I don't need
police tailing me everywhere.

391
00:48:17,320 --> 00:48:19,000
- Third--
- Enough.

392
00:48:20,000 --> 00:48:23,600
I can't do this. I can't do that.
How annoying. Where I go is my business.

393
00:48:29,920 --> 00:48:31,480
Did I say something wrong?

394
00:48:31,560 --> 00:48:34,360
You didn't do anything wrong.
Duen's just like this.

395
00:48:34,440 --> 00:48:36,160
Please don't take it personally.

396
00:49:23,320 --> 00:49:24,480
Lasor!

397
00:49:50,160 --> 00:49:51,160
Lasor!

398
00:49:56,080 --> 00:49:58,240
Stop right there. Don't move.

399
00:50:01,320 --> 00:50:03,160
Say what you came to say.

400
00:50:03,240 --> 00:50:04,720
I brought the head of Bandit Pud,

401
00:50:05,480 --> 00:50:08,320
the one who killed Khun Yod Pakdee,
to present to Your Excellency.

402
00:50:10,720 --> 00:50:14,280
Lasor, you're acting as a vigilante.

403
00:50:14,880 --> 00:50:16,320
Killing Bandit Pud is a crime.

404
00:50:16,400 --> 00:50:18,400
Come with me to the station now.

405
00:50:23,160 --> 00:50:24,800
So I'm under arrest?

406
00:50:31,840 --> 00:50:34,760
Leave. I'll talk to him.

407
00:50:37,080 --> 00:50:39,080
But he's a dangerous criminal, sir.

408
00:50:40,160 --> 00:50:41,400
Get out.

409
00:50:43,640 --> 00:50:44,720
Go!

410
00:50:52,800 --> 00:50:55,040
Pud robbed and slaughtered families.

411
00:50:56,800 --> 00:50:59,120
A wicked bandit like him deserved to die.

412
00:50:59,800 --> 00:51:04,560
Not bandit Wad and his son Lasor, sir?

413
00:51:06,160 --> 00:51:10,440
Pud was behind everything.
Khun Yod's murder,

414
00:51:11,720 --> 00:51:14,760
and the raid that destroyed
Bandit Wad's Chum Suea.

415
00:51:14,840 --> 00:51:16,920
I had nothing to do with this.

416
00:51:21,440 --> 00:51:22,400
Are you sure

417
00:51:23,880 --> 00:51:25,720
you had nothing to do with it?

418
00:51:26,600 --> 00:51:27,440
I'm sure.

419
00:51:28,960 --> 00:51:31,720
You and I were never enemies.

420
00:51:32,800 --> 00:51:35,360
You wanted to study at Khao Phrom,

421
00:51:35,440 --> 00:51:37,560
I even wrote you
a letter of recommendation.

422
00:51:38,760 --> 00:51:41,600
Tell me what you want.

423
00:51:42,400 --> 00:51:44,000
I'll give you anything.

424
00:51:50,480 --> 00:51:54,000
I want justice.

425
00:51:55,280 --> 00:51:58,960
I want my name and my father's cleared
for crimes we didn't commit.

426
00:52:00,520 --> 00:52:01,640
Can you do that?

427
00:52:04,320 --> 00:52:07,480
Of course. His Excellency and I

428
00:52:08,000 --> 00:52:10,160
will clear your names.

429
00:52:14,760 --> 00:52:17,960
Good. Don't you dare

430
00:52:19,800 --> 00:52:21,160
break your word.

431
00:52:23,440 --> 00:52:25,240
Otherwise, I'll rip out your tongues

432
00:52:26,320 --> 00:52:28,040
and feed them to dogs.

433
00:52:38,720 --> 00:52:41,040
The Governor announced that Bandit Pud

434
00:52:41,120 --> 00:52:43,520
slaughtered Khun Yod Pakdee's
entire household.

435
00:52:43,600 --> 00:52:47,400
Wasn't it Bandit Wad and his son Lasor?

436
00:52:47,480 --> 00:52:49,480
No. It was Bandit Wad's son

437
00:52:49,560 --> 00:52:52,000
who took down Bandit Pud.

438
00:52:52,080 --> 00:52:55,200
Seriously? How did it flip like this?

439
00:52:55,280 --> 00:52:58,960
Good bandits became bad bandits,
and bad bandits became good bandits.

440
00:52:59,560 --> 00:53:02,640
They say the governor's going to
reward Lasor

441
00:53:02,720 --> 00:53:03,680
and appoint him

442
00:53:03,760 --> 00:53:07,600
as the new Village Chief
of Khuan Phra-ngam, replacing Pud.

443
00:53:08,200 --> 00:53:11,840
Things you never thought you'd see,
you're seeing them now.

444
00:53:11,920 --> 00:53:13,320
I think so too.

445
00:53:14,440 --> 00:53:17,640
I don't agree. Lasor is a bandit,

446
00:53:17,720 --> 00:53:20,800
yet you're appointing him
as your governor's assistant.

447
00:53:22,000 --> 00:53:24,960
Tha Khiri is crawling with bandit dens.

448
00:53:25,040 --> 00:53:27,120
I need someone the people fear

449
00:53:27,200 --> 00:53:29,280
to keep this city under control.

450
00:53:30,200 --> 00:53:32,520
Using bandits to rule over bandits?

451
00:53:33,480 --> 00:53:37,560
Yes. Who understands bandits better
than bandits themselves?

452
00:53:38,160 --> 00:53:40,760
Let them deal with their own kind.
That's the best way.

453
00:53:41,440 --> 00:53:43,840
And we benefit from it too.

454
00:53:43,920 --> 00:53:48,120
You're keeping a cobra at your side.
One day, it'll turn and bite you.

455
00:54:04,720 --> 00:54:07,360
It's been a long time, Lady Duen.

456
00:54:08,560 --> 00:54:12,120
I thought you'd have died
a horrible death by now, Lasor.

457
00:54:13,480 --> 00:54:15,240
If I died,

458
00:54:16,080 --> 00:54:18,000
you wouldn't get to see my face again.

459
00:54:19,480 --> 00:54:23,040
A bandit like you must die
so the land can rise higher.

460
00:54:26,560 --> 00:54:29,360
Bandit this, bandit that.

461
00:54:32,080 --> 00:54:33,440
Even if I'm a bandit,

462
00:54:34,320 --> 00:54:38,480
I've got blood, flesh, and a heart,
no different from yours.

463
00:54:41,480 --> 00:54:43,120
If you don't believe me…

464
00:54:47,400 --> 00:54:48,880
you can try touching for yourself.

465
00:54:49,480 --> 00:54:51,320
Let go of me!

466
00:55:02,280 --> 00:55:05,440
- You should've spoken to him nicely.
- Why should I speak nicely to him?

467
00:55:05,520 --> 00:55:09,520
Look at him.
He's terrifying and disgusting.

468
00:55:09,600 --> 00:55:11,440
Just talking about him gives me chills.

469
00:55:11,520 --> 00:55:13,720
Then he must have something good in him.

470
00:55:13,800 --> 00:55:16,000
That's why Father appointed him
as a close aide.

471
00:55:16,760 --> 00:55:19,480
Is there really
no one better in Tha Khiri,

472
00:55:19,560 --> 00:55:23,600
that we have to let that damned Lasor
be governor's assistant?

473
00:55:23,680 --> 00:55:27,640
Lasor might look scary, but I still think
he's better than Bandit Pud.

474
00:55:27,720 --> 00:55:30,000
They're both evil.

475
00:55:40,520 --> 00:55:43,600
Once we cross this mountain,
we'll be in Huai Yao.

476
00:55:49,040 --> 00:55:53,000
You've finished studying at Khao Phrom.
You've found the Lek Lai.

477
00:55:53,080 --> 00:55:54,480
What will you do next?

478
00:55:59,040 --> 00:56:00,200
Go ask for your hand.

479
00:56:05,160 --> 00:56:07,360
Or do you not want to marry me anymore?

480
00:56:10,720 --> 00:56:11,960
I do.

481
00:56:15,120 --> 00:56:17,120
But before I go ask for your hand,

482
00:56:18,680 --> 00:56:21,040
there's something important
I still have to settle.

483
00:56:23,880 --> 00:56:25,600
More important than me?

484
00:56:26,520 --> 00:56:27,720
It's not like that.

485
00:56:29,200 --> 00:56:32,840
But it's something I must do
for my family.

486
00:56:34,840 --> 00:56:38,400
Blur, take me to meet your family.

487
00:56:46,120 --> 00:56:50,560
My father, mother, and little sister

488
00:56:51,840 --> 00:56:53,760
were all murdered.

489
00:57:09,400 --> 00:57:13,880
If you catch that bandit,
you'll hand him over to the police, right?

490
00:57:13,960 --> 00:57:18,160
<i>If there's no justice in this world,</i>
<i>then I'll use my way.</i>

491
00:57:18,240 --> 00:57:21,040
An eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth.

492
00:57:21,120 --> 00:57:22,480
<i>You disappeared for an entire year.</i>

493
00:57:22,560 --> 00:57:25,800
And now you're Sir Lasor,
Governor's Assistant?

494
00:57:25,880 --> 00:57:29,120
<i>Both Bandit Wad and Lasor have been</i>
<i>completely cleared of all charges.</i>

495
00:57:29,200 --> 00:57:33,120
I am Khun Yod's son,
Village Chief of Khuan Phra-ngam.

496
00:57:33,200 --> 00:57:37,680
<i>Khun Yod's son isn't dead.</i>
<i>Can you tell me where to find him?</i>

497
00:57:37,760 --> 00:57:39,320
I want to meet him.

498
00:57:39,920 --> 00:57:41,720
<i>Why does my body</i>

499
00:57:41,800 --> 00:57:44,160
<i>feel like it's burning alive, Old Master?</i>

500
00:57:44,240 --> 00:57:47,480
Your mind is restless. In turmoil.

501
00:57:47,560 --> 00:57:50,280
<i>There is no Blur anymore. Only Yiam.</i>

502
00:57:50,360 --> 00:57:53,400
Khun Yod's son, whose entire family
was slaughtered by Bandit Wad and his son.

503
00:58:37,080 --> 00:58:40,680
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
